The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem related to revenue maximization, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves partitioning a binary matrix, which is a common topic in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses linear programming and duality arguments, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
